wiki.content: "SNAP" is a song by Armenian singer Rosa Linn, released on March 19, 2022. The song was written and composed by Linn, with Larzz Principato, Courtney Harrell, Allie Crystal and Tamar Kaprelian. The song represented Armenia in the Eurovision Song Contest 2022 in Turin, Italy. At Eurovision, Rosa Linn became the first artist to qualify for the final for Armenia since 2017, finishing in 20th place with 61 points. Following the contest, the song went viral on social media platform TikTok. "SNAP" reached the top of the charts in the Flanders region of Belgium, the top ten in Austria, Netherlands, Ireland, Norway, Sweden and Switzerland. The song also reached the charts in 23 other music markets, including peaking at number 23 on the UK Singles Chart, making Rosa Linn the highest-charting foreign act from Eurovision 2022 in the UK. It also debuted on the US Billboard Hot 100 at number 97, becoming the second Eurovision song of the 21st century to enter the chart. Read more on Last.fm.
